  "prompt": "3 digit no unit digit, ten digit and hundred digit their ratio 3:5:7 if the difference of original number and \u0155eversing the digit is 396 find the no?",
  "response": "Let's denote the three-digit number as \\( \\overline{abc} \\), where \\( a \\), \\( b \\), and \\( c \\) are the hundreds, tens, and units digits, respectively. According to the problem, the ratio of the digits \\( c : b : a = 3 : 5 : 7 \\).\n\nLet the digits be \\( c = 3k \\), \\( b = 5k \\), and \\( a = 7k \\) for some positive integer \\( k \\).\n\nThus, the original number can be expressed as:\n\\[\n100a + 10b + c = 100(7k) + 10(5k) + 3k = 700k + 50k + 3k = 753k\n\\]\n\nWhen the digits are reversed, the new number is:\n\\[\n100c + 10b + a = 100(3k) + 10(5k) + 7k = 300k + 50k + 7k = 357k\n\\]\n\nAccording to the problem, the difference between the original number and the reversed number is 396:\n\\[\n753k - 357k = 396\n\\]\n\nThis simplifies to:\n\\[\n396k = 396\n\\]\n\\[\nk = 1\n\\]\n\nSubstituting \\( k = 1 \\) back into the expressions for the digits:\n\\[\nc = 3k = 3 \\times 1 = 3\n\\]\n\\[\nb = 5k = 5 \\times 1 = 5\n\\]\n\\[\na = 7k = 7 \\times 1 = 7\n\\]\n\nThus, the original number is \\( \\overline{abc} = \\overline{753} \\).\n\nThe number is \\( 753 \\).",
